            <h2 class="blog-post-title" style="margin-top:3rem;">What is Alcohol Addiction or Alcoholism?</h2>
            <p class="lead" style="">
                Alcoholism commonly known as alcohol use disorder is the most severe form of alcohol abuse and involves the inability to manage and control drinking habits due to physical and emotional substance. Those with alcoholism have a daily urge to drink despite related legal and health issues. When a person is dependent on alcohol, changes are observed in the brain which includes physical withdrawals like insomnia, nausea, sweating, anxiety, and physical discomfort if a person doesn’t drink. Alcohol use disorder is further classified into three categories: mild, moderate, and severe and each of it has various symptoms and can cause harmful side effects.
            </p>
